All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary Enum Summary Exception Summary 
    Class Description
    AccessTime
    This class holds the start and end date of a student's access period.
    AccountType
    Represents the different account types that can access the Stars Application.
    AdminController
    This class is responsible for handling tasks related to the admin panel.
    AdminUi
    This class is responsible for the logic of getting input and output from the user for tasks related to the admin panel.
    ClashingRegisteredIndexNumberException
    This is a class that extends Exception which is thrown when there is a clash between registered index numbers and the index number a student is currently trying to register.
    ClashingWaitListedIndexNumberException
    This is a class that extends Exception which is thrown when there is a clash between waitlisted index numbers and the index number a student is currently trying to register.
    Course
    This class is responsible for modelling a course which details the attributes and methods of each * Course object part of the STARS Planner system.
    CourseInWaitListException
    This is a class that extends Exception which is thrown when the course the student is trying to register for is already in wait-list.
    CourseRegisteredException
    This is a class that extends Exception which is thrown when the course the student is trying to register for is already registered for them.
    EmailNotification
    This is a Singleton class that is responsible for handling the logic of sending notification via E-mail implementing INotification.
    ErrorMessage
    This class contains all the error messages displayed in the program.
    Gender
    This is one of the enum data types we created - Gender The pre-defined group of constants under our Gender data type are: MALE, FEMALE since there are generally 2 types of gender: male and female.
    ILoginable
    This interface is an abstraction of the methods that any class providing the login logic should implement.
    ILoginInfoFileManager
    This interface is an abstraction of the methods that any class providing the logic to retrieve and store login information should implement.
    IndexNumber
    This class is responsible for modelling the index number of a course which details the attributes and methods of each IndexNumber object for a particular Course object.
    INotification
    This is an interface which sends an email notification detailing the pending/actual outcome of the student's actions when he or she uses the STARS Planner.
    InvalidAccessTimeException
    This is a class that extends Exception which is thrown when the course the student is trying to access STARS Application past their end date and time.
    InvalidLessonTypeException
    This is a class that extends Exception which is thrown when the lesson type is anything other than LAB, LECTURE or TUTORIAL.
    InvalidNewMaxException
    This is a class that extends Exception which is thrown when the maximum vacancy for a particular Index Number of a particular Course is less than 1 or contains special characters.
    IStorageManager
    This interface contains the abstraction of the methods that any class providing the logic to retrieve and store data should implement.
    Lesson
    This class is responsible for modelling a lesson which details the attributes and methods of each Lesson object.
    LessonType
    This is one of the enum data types we created - LessonType The pre-defined group of constants under our Gender data type are: LECTURE, LAB, TUTORIAL since there are generally 3 types of lessons: lecture, lab and tutorial.
    LoginController
    This class is responsible for handling the login process.
    LoginInfo
    This class is responsible for modelling LoginInfo which details the attributes and methods of each LoginInfo object from a particular user logging into the STARS Planner.
    LoginInfoFileManager
    This class is responsible for the logic that handles the storage and retrieval of login information.
    LoginManager
    This class is responsible for handling the login logic.
    LoginUi
    This class is responsible for the logic of getting input and output from the user for their login information.
    Main
    The main entry point for the program.
    MaxAuExceededException
    This is a class that extends Exception which is thrown when the student attempts to register a course that will cause them to break their maximum vacancy ceiling.
    NoVacancyException
    This is a class that extends Exception which is thrown when there is no vacancy in the particular Index Number of a particular Course.
    NoVacancySwapException
    This is a class that extends Exception which is thrown when there is no vacancy in the particular Index Number of a particular Course that the student is trying to swap their own registered Index Number with.
    PeerClashingRegisteredIndexNumberException
    This is a class that extends Exception which is thrown when the timetable of the registered Index Number of peer clashes with the student's own index number's timetable.
    PeerClashingWaitListedIndexNumberException
    This is a class that extends Exception which is thrown when the timetable of the waitlisted Index Number of peer clashes with the student's own index number's timetable.
    SameIndexNumberSwapException
    This is a class that extends Exception which is thrown when the student attempts to swap Index Number with the same Index Number from the same Course.
    School
    This is one of the enum data types we created - School The pre-defined group of constants under our Gender data type are: SSS, ADM, SCSE In reality, there are obviously more schools in NTU not covered by our programme.
    SHA256Hasher
    This class is responsible for the logic of hashing a password.
    Storage
    This class is responsible for storing and retrieving all the Student objects and Course objects in the program.
    StorageManager
    This class is responsible for the persistency of a Storage object.
    Student
    This class is responsible for modelling Student which details the attributes and methods of each Student object part of the STARS Planner system.
    StudentController
    This class is responsible for handling all the tasks related to the student panel.
    StudentUi
    This class is responsible for the logic of getting input and output from the user for tasks related to the Student panel.
    TimeTable
    This class is responsible for managing all the index numbers that a particular Student object is registered or in the wait list for.
    Ui
    The base class for all Ui classes.
    WrongAccessPeriodException
    This is a class that extends Exception which is thrown when the course the student is trying to access STARS Application outside of their access period.
    WrongLoginInfoException
    This is a class that extends Exception which is thrown when the LoginInfo is inaccurate.
